  <main id="main-content">
  <section class="ps-page-header" data-visual-master="ergonomic-height-live-fit-v1">
    <div class="ps-container ps-page-header__grid">
      <div><span class="ps-kicker">Workspace Lab · Live fit</span>
      <h1 class="ps-page-header__title">Find your starting heights.</h1>
      <p class="ps-lede">Translate body height into transparent desk, chair, keyboard, and monitor ranges—then tune for comfort.</p></div>
      <div class="ps-measure" aria-label="Six live measurements"><span class="ps-measure__rail" aria-hidden="true"></span><span class="ps-measure__value">6 live fit readings</span></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="ehc-tool">
    <div class="ehc-layout">
      <!-- Left: Input -->
      <div class="ehc-card ehc-animate">
        <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:1.3rem;margin-bottom:var(--space-md);">Your Height</h2>

        <div class="ehc-unit-toggle" id="unitToggle" role="group" aria-label="Measurement unit">
          <button type="button" class="ehc-unit-btn active" data-unit="imperial" aria-pressed="true" onclick="ehcSetUnit('imperial')">ft / in</button>
          <button type="button" class="ehc-unit-btn" data-unit="metric" aria-pressed="false" onclick="ehcSetUnit('metric')">cm</button>
        </div>

        <div class="ehc-height-display" id="heightDisplay">5'9"</div>

        <label class="sr-only" for="heightSlider">Your height</label>

        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:var(--space-md);">
          <span style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--c-text-muted);" id="heightMinLabel">4'0"</span>
          <input type="range" class="ehc-slider" id="heightSlider" aria-describedby="heightDisplay" min="48" max="84" value="69" step="0.5" style="flex:1;">
          <span style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--c-text-muted);" id="heightMaxLabel">7'0"</span>
        </div>

        <p class="form-hint" style="margin-top:var(--space-sm);">Drag to adjust. Measurements update in real time.</p>

        <!-- SVG Illustration -->
        <div class="ehc-svg-wrap ps-fit-zone" style="margin-top:var(--space-lg);" aria-label="Live workstation fit diagram derived from the calculator outputs">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 200 320" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" id="ehcSvg">
            <!-- Floor -->
            <line x1="10" y1="300" x2="190" y2="300" stroke="var(--c-border)" stroke-width="2"/>
            <!-- Person body (proportions scale with height) -->
            <g id="personGroup">
              <!-- Head -->
              <circle id="ehcHead" cx="100" cy="75" r="18" fill="var(--c-primary-soft)" stroke="var(--c-primary)" stroke-width="2"/>
              <!-- Neck -->
              <line id="ehcNeck" x1="100" y1="93" x2="100" y2="108" stroke="var(--c-primary)" stroke-width="3"/>
              <!-- Torso -->
              <rect id="ehcTorso" x="88" y="108" width="24" height="55" rx="4" fill="var(--c-primary-soft)" stroke="var(--c-primary)" stroke-width="2"/>
              <!-- Arms -->
              <line id="ehcArmL" x1="88" y1="120" x2="60" y2="155" stroke="var(--c-primary)" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              <line id="ehcArmR" x1="112" y1="120" x2="140" y2="155" stroke="var(--c-primary)" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              <!-- Desk surface -->
              <rect id="ehcDeskSurface" x="20" y="155" width="160" height="6" rx="2" fill="var(--c-accent)" opacity="0.7"/>
              <!-- Desk legs -->
              <line id="ehcDeskLegL" x1="40" y1="161" x2="40" y2="300" stroke="var(--c-text-muted)" stroke-width="2" opacity="0.4"/>
              <line id="ehcDeskLegR" x1="160" y1="161" x2="160" y2="300" stroke="var(--c-text-muted)" stroke-width="2" opacity="0.4"/>
              <!-- Monitor -->
              <rect id="ehcMonitor" x="130" y="85" width="45" height="35" rx="3" fill="var(--c-accent-soft)" stroke="var(--c-accent)" stroke-width="2"/>
              <!-- Monitor stand -->
              <line id="ehcMonitorStand" x1="152" y1="120" x2="152" y2="155" stroke="var(--c-accent)" stroke-width="2"/>
              <!-- Eye level line -->
              <line id="ehcEyeLine" x1="10" y1="75" x2="190" y2="75" stroke="var(--c-primary)" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4 4" opacity="0.5"/>
              <text x="8" y="78" font-size="8" fill="var(--c-text-muted)">eye level</text>
            </g>
          </svg>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Right: Results -->
      <div class="ehc-results ehc-animate blueprint-panel" id="ehcResults">
        <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:1.3rem;margin-bottom:var(--space-sm);">Your Estimated Starting Ranges</h2>
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--c-text-light);margin-bottom:var(--space-md);">Use each point estimate as a starting place, then adjust within the range until your posture feels supported.</p>

        <div class="ehc-result-row ehc-result-highlight">
          <div><span class="ehc-result-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><path d="M5 20h14M7 17V7h10v10M4 7h16M12 4v16"/></svg></span><span class="ehc-result-label">Standing Desk Height <small>Keyboard surface for standing</small></span></div>
          <div class="ehc-result-output"><span class="ehc-result-value" id="standingDesk">38.0</span><span class="ehc-result-unit" id="standingDeskUnit">in</span><small class="ehc-result-range" id="standingDeskRange">Range 37.0–39.0 in</small></div>
        </div>

        <div class="ehc-result-row">
          <div><span class="ehc-result-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><path d="M5 20h14M7 17V7h10v10M4 7h16M12 4v16"/></svg></span><span class="ehc-result-label">Sitting Desk Height <small>Keyboard surface for sitting</small></span></div>
          <div class="ehc-result-output"><span class="ehc-result-value" id="sittingDesk">27.9</span><span class="ehc-result-unit" id="sittingDeskUnit">in</span><small class="ehc-result-range" id="sittingDeskRange">Range 26.9–28.9 in</small></div>
        </div>

        <div class="ehc-result-row ehc-result-highlight">
          <div><span class="ehc-result-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><path d="M6 13h12v7M8 13V7h8v6M6 20v2m12-2v2"/></svg></span><span class="ehc-result-label">Chair Seat Height <small>Top of seat cushion</small></span></div>
          <div class="ehc-result-output"><span class="ehc-result-value" id="chairHeight">17.3</span><span class="ehc-result-unit" id="chairHeightUnit">in</span><small class="ehc-result-range" id="chairHeightRange">Range 16.8–17.8 in</small></div>
        </div>

        <div class="ehc-result-row">
          <div><span class="ehc-result-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><rect x="3" y="4" width="18" height="12" rx="1"/><path d="M12 16v4M8 20h8"/></svg></span><span class="ehc-result-label">Monitor Height <small>Top of screen at eye level</small></span></div>
          <div class="ehc-result-output"><span class="ehc-result-value" id="monitorHeight">48.3</span><span class="ehc-result-unit" id="monitorHeightUnit">in</span><small class="ehc-result-range" id="monitorHeightRange">Range 47.3–49.3 in</small></div>
        </div>

        <div class="ehc-result-row">
          <div><span class="ehc-result-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><path d="M3 12h18M3 8v8M21 8v8M7 10v4m4-4v4m4-4v4"/></svg></span><span class="ehc-result-label">Monitor Distance <small>Arm's length from eyes</small></span></div>
          <div class="ehc-result-output"><span class="ehc-result-value" id="monitorDistance">22.8</span><span class="ehc-result-unit" id="monitorDistanceUnit">in</span><small class="ehc-result-range" id="monitorDistanceRange">Range 20.8–24.8 in</small></div>
        </div>

        <div class="ehc-result-row">
          <div><span class="ehc-result-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><rect x="3" y="7" width="18" height="11" rx="1"/><path d="M6 11h2m2 0h2m2 0h2m2 0h1M7 15h10"/></svg></span><span class="ehc-result-label">Keyboard Height <small>Elbows at 90°, wrists straight</small></span></div>
          <div class="ehc-result-output"><span class="ehc-result-value" id="keyboardHeight">27.9</span><span class="ehc-result-unit" id="keyboardHeightUnit">in</span><small class="ehc-result-range" id="keyboardHeightRange">Range 26.9–28.9 in</small></div>
        </div>

        <div class="ehc-actions">
          <button type="button" class="ehc-action-btn ehc-action-btn--primary" onclick="ehcPrint()">Print Estimates</button>
          <button type="button" class="ehc-action-btn" onclick="ehcCopyResults(this)">Copy Results</button>
          <button type="button" class="ehc-action-btn" onclick="ehcShareTwitter()">𝕏 Share on X</button>
          <button type="button" class="ehc-action-btn" onclick="ehcShareFB()">f Share on Facebook</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Info / tips section -->
    <div class="ehc-info">
      <h3>How These Measurements Work</h3>
      <p style="margin-bottom:var(--space-md);color:var(--c-text-light);">The numerical coefficients below are transparent <strong>The Workspace Pro heuristics</strong>, not OSHA formulas. They turn standing height into estimated starting points; the displayed ranges encourage individual adjustment.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Standing desk height</strong> = standing height × 0.55, with a ±1 in adjustment range</li>
        <li><strong>Sitting desk and keyboard height</strong> = standing height × 0.405, with a ±1 in range</li>
        <li><strong>Chair seat height</strong> = standing height × 0.25, with a ±0.5 in range</li>
        <li><strong>Monitor top height while seated</strong> = standing height × 0.70, with a ±1 in range</li>
        <li><strong>Monitor distance</strong> = standing height × 0.33, limited to 18–28 in, with a ±2 in range inside those limits</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin-top:var(--space-md);color:var(--c-text-light);">For posture checkpoints, see OSHA's <a href="https://www.osha.gov/etools/computer-workstations" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Computer Workstations eTool</a>, including its current guidance for <a href="https://www.osha.gov/etools/computer-workstations/components/chairs" target="_blank" rel="noopener">chairs</a> and <a href="https://www.osha.gov/etools/computer-workstations/components/monitors" target="_blank" rel="noopener">monitors</a>. OSHA notes that no single posture or component arrangement fits everyone.</p>
      <div class="ehc-tip">
        <strong>Important:</strong> These estimates are educational starting points, not medical advice or an individual fitting. Body proportions, footwear, equipment, vision, mobility, and health needs can change a comfortable setup. Adjust for comfort and neutral posture; consult a qualified clinician or ergonomics professional for pain, injury, disability, or specialized needs.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="ps-section ps-section--compact" aria-labelledby="height-method-title"><div class="ps-container"><div class="ps-evidence">
    <div class="ps-evidence__label">Fit method</div>
    <div class="ps-evidence__body"><h2 id="height-method-title">One calculation source, six visible readings</h2><p>The diagram and result rows read the same tested height outputs. They are adjustable starting ranges—not a diagnosis or a promise of one perfect posture.</p><p class="ps-evidence__source">Evidence rail: transparent Workspace Pro heuristics plus OSHA posture checkpoints linked above.</p></div>
  </div></div></section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="cta-section" style="max-width:var(--max-width);margin:var(--space-2xl) auto;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Need help setting up your workspace?</h2>
      <p>Take our full ergonomic workspace assessment for personalized product recommendations, a setup checklist, and expert advice tailored to your body and work style.</p>
      <a href="/#assessment" class="btn btn--secondary btn--lg">Take Our Workspace Assessment →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="newsletter-bar" id="newsletter">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="newsletter-bar__title">Get Weekly Workspace Tips</h2>
      <p class="newsletter-bar__desc">Personalized advice, gear deals, and ergonomic tips — every Wednesday. No spam, unsubscribe anytime.</p>
      <div class="newsletter-form">
        <a href="https://theworkspacepro.beehiiv.com/subscribe" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn--primary">Subscribe Free →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

    </main>
